Rod McKie says he is seeking new sites on trunk roads
Times photographer, Nick Ray
Dominic Walsh
Published at 12:01AM, January 19 2013
Britain’s biggest motorway services operator has completed a £350 million refinancing of its debt facilities to give it a platform to press ahead with expansion.
Welcome Break, which runs 29 sites with a turnover of more than £600 million, said that it had secured £221 million of senior debt from a consortium of eight banks and £130 million of mezzanine finance from GSO Capital Partners, the credit division of Blackstone.
Rod McKie, the chief executive, said he was seeking new sites on trunk roads and was upgrading its existing sites with brands including Starbucks, Waitrose and Days Inn.
